Larrakia Country • Darwin

Turn Darwin’s plastic into useful things — together.

A simple community micro‑factory where locals learn, collect, and make with recycled plastic.

Join the crew See how it works

Local recycling matters in the NT.

Processing plastic here reduces transport, builds skills, and keeps value in the Territory. We keep it clean, small‑scale and educational.

How it works

Three simple steps anyone can join.

1 · Collect

Set up home/school/business drop points and sort by type.

2 · Shred

Clean, identify ♻︎2/♻︎5, then shred into safe flakes.

3 · Make

Use small open‑source machines to create useful products.

A tiny workshop & collection point.

We operate a home micro‑factory with shredder, injection, sheet press and extrusion. Drop‑off (pilot): Saturdays 10:00–12:00. Address on confirmation.

Quick answers

Are you Precious Plastic HQ?

No. We’re a local initiative inspired by the global movement, tailored for Darwin.

What plastics can I bring?

Clean ♻︎2 (HDPE) and ♻︎5 (PP), sorted by type. Contact us for special ♻︎1 (PET) projects.

Do you sell products?

We make small‑batch items to fund education and community builds.
